clinicalDescription: Overview: blood sugar levels become high during pregnancy. Presentation: thirsty, hungrier, urinary frequency; can have excess weight gain; can have no symptoms. Assessment:Usually happens in the second half of pregnancy (24 - 28 wks). glucose challenge or glucose screening test. Plan: Women with class A1 can manage it through diet and exercise. Those who have class A2 need to take insulin or other medications. Blood sugar monitoring. Lifestyle changes, diet. Prognosis: Gestational diabetes goes away after you give birth. Higher risk of developing type 2 diabetes later in life.
